// This  file contains mongo db installation and configuration 

Download MongoDB NoSQL Database 2.6 form: https://www.mongodb.com/download-center

Then install the database.

Creating connection:

Create a directory to store mongo database collections
eg: D:\username\Documents\data\db

Run CMD and change the directory to  C:\Program Files\MongoDB\Server\3.4\bin
then enter
mongod --dbpath D:\username\Documents\data\db

then enter
mongo


For the MongoDB client you can robomongo

using  robomongo you can:

create database
create collection(=table)
CRUD into the  collection





